<PubmedArticleSet>
<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41058492</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>08</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>08</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Print">0028-2200</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>132</Volume><Issue>10</Issue><PubDate><Year>2025</Year><Month>Oct</Month><Day>07</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Nederlands tijdschrift voor tandheelkunde</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Ned Tijdschr Tandheelkd</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>[Sports drinks and dental erosion].</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>464</StartPage><EndPage>469</EndPage><MedlinePgn>464-469</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.5177/ntvt.2025.10.25020</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>The consumption of sports drinks has increased significantly in recent decades. These drinks are promoted for their ability to improve hydration, replenish electrolytes and provide energy during intense physical exertion. Sports drinks often have low pH and high buffering capacity in addition to high concentrations of sugars, which can be potentially detrimental to the dentition. A number of scientific studies have examined the relationship between sports drinks consumption and tooth wear. Given that erosive dental wear has multifactorial causes, sports drinks appear to be only one of the possible contributing factors.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Gambon</LastName><ForeName>D L</ForeName><Initials>DL</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Pediatric Dentistry, Centre of Dentistry and Oral Healthcare, University Medical Centre Groningen, Groningen, the Netherlands.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author></AuthorList><Language>dut</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType><PublicationType UI="D016454">Review</PublicationType><PublicationType UI="D004740">English Abstract</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList><VernacularTitle>Sportdranken en erosieve gebitsslijtage.</VernacularTitle></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>Netherlands</Country><MedlineTA>Ned Tijdschr Tandheelkd</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>0400771</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>0028-2200</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><CitationSubset>IM</CitationSubset><MeshHeadingList><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D006801" MajorTopicYN="N">Humans</DescriptorName></MeshHeading><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D014077" MajorTopicYN="Y">Tooth Erosion</DescriptorName><QualifierName UI="Q000209" MajorTopicYN="N">etiology</QualifierName><QualifierName UI="Q000453" MajorTopicYN="N">epidemiology</QualifierName><QualifierName UI="Q000139" MajorTopicYN="N">chemically induced</QualifierName></MeshHeading><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D001628" MajorTopicYN="Y">Beverages</DescriptorName><QualifierName UI="Q000009" MajorTopicYN="N">adverse effects</QualifierName></MeshHeading><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D006863" MajorTopicYN="N">Hydrogen-Ion Concentration</DescriptorName></MeshHeading><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D013177" MajorTopicYN="Y">Sports</DescriptorName></MeshHeading><MeshHeading><DescriptorName UI="D061215" MajorTopicYN="N">Energy Drinks</DescriptorName><QualifierName UI="Q000009" MajorTopicYN="N">adverse effects</QualifierName></MeshHeading></MeshHeadingList><OtherAbstract Type="Publisher" Language="dut"><AbstractText>De consumptie van sportdranken is de afgelopen decennia aanzienlijk toegenomen. Deze dranken worden gepromoot vanwege hun vermogen om hydratatie te verbeteren, elektrolyten aan te vullen en energie te leveren tijdens intensieve lichamelijke inspanning. Sportdranken hebben vaak een lage pH en een hoge buffercapaciteit naast een hoge concentratie aan suikers, wat potentieel schadelijk kan zijn voor het gebit. Een aantal wetenschappelijke onderzoeken heeft het verband tussen de consumptie van sportdranken en gebitsslijtage onderzocht. Aangezien erosieve gebitsslijtage multifactori le oorzaken kent, lijkt sportdrank slechts een van de mogelijke factoren te zijn.</AbstractText></OtherAbstract></MedlineCitation><PubmedData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="medline"><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>8</Day><Hour>6</Hour><Minute>30</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="pubmed"><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>8</Day><Hour>6</Hour><Minute>29</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="entrez"><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>8</Day><Hour>4</Hour><Minute>13</Minute></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>ppublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">41058492</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="doi">10.5177/ntvt.2025.10.25020</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></PubmedData></PubmedArticle></PubmedArticleSet>